  "description": "Proleptic-Gregorian ordinal core from CPython's _pydatetime: isLeap/daysInMonth/ymd2ord/ord2ymd/weekday/validDate with an anchored order-isomorphism spec set (epoch anchor + unit step + strict monotonicity) for ymd2ord and frozen divisibility/table anchors for the leap rule and month lengths. `ord2ymd` is the inverse API (CPython's `_ord2ymd`), specced as a left/right inverse of `ymd2ord`. Includes hidden-invariant hardening specs proved via strengthened induction hypotheses kept out of the spec statements: year-boundary telescoping (Dec-31 successor, whole-year span), exact inter-year ordinal gap and leap-density bridge to a frozen leap counter, dual ≤366/≥365 gap bounds, multi-year weekday threading mod 7, and `ord2ymd` as a strictly increasing calendar walk (year-band, Jan-1 grounding, strict monotonicity, and the one-day immediate-successor step). Adds order-isomorphism biconditionals whose reverse directions hide trichotomy/injectivity and successor-reconstruction arguments (strict-order iff, immediate-successor iff), the inverse month-band uniqueness (the month analogue of the year band), and a mod-7 weekday-congruence coupling.",
